Similarity Similarity between chemicals is described by an integrated similarity index (SI) ranging from 1 (maximum similarity) to 0 (minimum similarity), resulting from a weighted combination of a binary fingerprint array and three non-binary structural keys, as follow:SI=SFP0.4∗SCD0.35∗SHE0.1∗SFG0.15\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
